{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κόλπος</b>, ὁ, <br /> <b>bosom, lap</b>, παῖδ᾽ ἐπὶ κόλπῳ ἔχουσα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 6.400; ἂψ ὁ πάϊς πρὸς κόλπον ἐκλίνθη [prev. work] 467; ἡ δ᾽ ἄρα μιν κηώδεϊ δέξατο κόλπῳ (compare 111.1) [prev. work] 483 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἱμάντα τέῳ ἐγκάτθεο κ. put the girdle in thy <b>bosom</b>,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 14.219; εἰς κόλπον πτύσαι 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Characteres” 16.15 (compare πτύω); ἐν κόλπῳ εἶχες ὄφιν 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 602; ὁ κ. Αβραάμ NT.Luke.16.22 \">NT+6th c.BC+</a>]; frequently of pet birds or animals, τρέφειν ἐν κ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Herodas Mimographus 6.102 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; κυνίδιον ἐν κόλπῳ τιθηνούμενον <b>lap</b>-dog, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.472c; κίσσαν ἐκ μέσων τῶν κόλπων ἁρπάσας 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Jud.Voc.” 8; so τὸ θυγάτριον ἐκ κόλπων τῶν ἐμῶν ἀναρπάσαντα 3rd c.AD: Heliodorus Scriptor Eroticus 4.14: _metaphorically_, εἰς τοὺς εὐανθεῖς κ. λειμώνων 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 373 (Lyric poetry); λειμώνων φύλλων τ᾽ ἐν κόλποις ναίω [prev. author] “Av.” 1094 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also τὰ ὑπὸ κόλπου, ={τὰ ἀφροδίσια}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Alex.” 39. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> = {αἰδοῖον γυναικεῖον}, especially <b>vagina</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Soranus Medicus 1.16, +others, 2nd c.AD: Rufus Medicus “περὶ ὀνομασίας” 196, 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 2.222: _plural_, 2nd c.AD: Soranus Medicus 1.70b, 2nd c.AD: Sextus Empiricus Philosophus “adversus Mathematicos” 5.62. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] <br /><Level4><b>__2.b</b></Level4> κόλποι τῆς ὑστέρας supposed <b>sinuses</b> in the womb, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ φύσιος παιδίου” 31, 2nd c.AD: Soranus Medicus 1.9 (_sing._), 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus “de Usu Partium” 14.4. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <br /><Level4><b>__2.c</b></Level4> in poets more vaguely of the whole <b>sinus genitalis, womb</b>, in <i>plural</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Helena” 1145 (Lyric poetry), 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Hymnus in Jovem” 15: _sing._, [prev. author] “Del.” 214; δεσποίνας ὑπὸ κόλπον ἔδυν 5th-6th c.AD: Orphica “Fragmenta” 32c. 8; θεὸς διὰ κόλπου [prev. work] 31i24 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>metaphorically</i>, of the grave, σῶμα σὸν ἐν κόλποις.. γαῖα καλύπτει [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 2.3839, compare 3412, “epigram Gr.” 214.7 (from Rhenea)\">Refs</a>]; κ. ἡμερῶν, of the <b>womb</b> of time, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Ezekiel Poeta Judaeus “Exagoge - Mnemosyne” 39. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>] <br /><Level4><b>__2.d</b></Level4> of other cavities, οἱ κ. τῆς κοιλίας, in the ἐχῖνος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 530b27 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; of the <b>ventricles</b> of the heart, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 2.216. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>fold of a garment</b>, especially as it fell over the girdle, frequently in <i>plural</i>, δεύοντο δὲ δάκρυσι κ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 9.570, compare 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 539 (_anapaest meter_)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], etc.: also in <i>singular</i>, κ. βαθὺν καταλιπόμενος τοῦ κιθῶνος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.125 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κόλπον ἀνιεμένη letting down the <b>bosom of her robe</b>, i.e. baring her breast, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 22.80; ἐπὶ σφυρὰ κόλπον ἀνεῖσαι 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 15.134 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; κρύψε δὲ παρθενίαν ὠδῖνα κόλποις, i.e. she concealed her pregnancy <b>by the loose folds of her robe</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 6.31; κατακρύψασ᾽ ὑπὸ κόλπῳ 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 15.469; κόλπῳ φέρουσα.. πεπλώματος 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 1044 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ὑπὸ κόλπου (variant -ῳ) χεῖρας ἔχειν 'keep one's hand in one's <b>pocket</b>', of a stingy person, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 16.16; ὑπὸ κόλπου 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Herm.” 37, 81, “Hes.” 2, “Merc.Cond.” 27 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; ὑπὸ κόλπον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus see at {μασχαλοληπτεῖ}, variant in 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Ind.” 12. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> any <b>bosom-like hollow</b>: <br /><Level3><b>__III.1</b></Level3> of the sea, first in a half-literal sense, of a sea-goddess, Θέτις δ᾽ ὑπεδέξατο κόλπῳ received him <b>in her bosom</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 6.136, compare above 1.1: generally, δῦτε θαλάσσης εὐρέα κ. 18.140, compare 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.435; εἴσω ἁλὸς εὐρέα κ. lines 21.125: in _plural_, κατὰ δεινοὺς κ. ἁλός 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 5.52; also κόλποι αἰθέρος 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 13.88; Ἐρέβους ἐν ἀπείροσι κ. 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 694. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> <b>bay, gulf</b>, Ἑρμιόνην Ἀσίνην τε, βαθὺν κατὰ κ. ἐχούσας, i.e. βαθὺν κατεχούσας κόλπον, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.560; Μηλιεὺς κ. 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 486 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; κ. Ῥέας, i.e. the Adriatic, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Pr.” 837; Τυρσηνικὸς κ. 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 598, compare 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.11, 7.58, 198, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.90, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.3</b></Level3> <b>vale</b>, κ. Ἀργεῖος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 4.49; Νεμέας [prev. author] “O.” 9.87, compare 14.23; Ἐλευσινίας Δηοῦς ἐν κόλποις 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 1121 (Lyric poetry); κ. Τροίας 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Troades” 130 (Lyric poetry); Πιερικὸς κ. 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.99, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 6.5.17. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.4</b></Level3> of a fortified site, <b>salient</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd-2nd c.BC: Philo Mechanicus “(Belopoeica) Excerpte aus Philons Mechanik - Ath. Berl. Akad.” 86.8. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.5</b></Level3> ὁ κ. τοῦ ἅρματος <b>bottom</b> of the chariot, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.1Ki.22.35. \">LXX</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.6</b></Level3> <b>fistulous ulcer</b> which spreads under the skin, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Dioscorides (Dioscurides) Medicus 1.128, 1st-2nd c.AD: Heliodorus Medicus cited in 4th c.AD: Oribasius Medicus 44.8.22, 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 11.125. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> in Tactics, <b>enveloping force</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Onosander (Onasander) Tacticus 21.5. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G2859","accentedUnicode":"κόλπος","shortDef":"lap area: side, bosom, chest; bay","mediumDef":"lap area: side, bosom, chest; bay <br /><b>the bosom,</b> <ref='Luk.16.22, 23'>Lk. 16:22, 23</ref>; <ref='Jhn.1.18; 13:23'>Jn. 1:18; 13:23</ref>; <b>the bosom of a garment,</b> <ref='Luk.6.38'>Lk. 6:38</ref>; <b>a bay, creek, inlet,</b> <ref='Act.27.39'>Acts 27:39</ref>*","stepGloss":"bosom","stepTransliteration":"kolpos","count":6,"_es_Definition":"seno, pecho ; regazo (LUC.6:38) ; bahía, golfo, ensenada (HCH.27:39) ; cercano, próximo, cerca (JN.1:18)","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 胸部<br>2) 衣摺 (路 6:38)<br>3) 海灣 (徒 27:39)","_zh_Definition":"1) 胸部<br>2) 衣折 (路 6:38)<br>3) 海湾 (徒 27:39)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"lồng ngực; lòng","_zh_tw_Gloss":"懷","_es_Gloss":"seno","_zh_Gloss":"怀"}]}